# {{.ProjectName}}

OpenCode workspace-config scaffold generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/plugin-kit-ai/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

This lane models the official OpenCode workspace config surfaces that fit the package-standard authoring model today.

## Status

- Target lane: `opencode`
- Platform family: `code_plugin`
- Launcher: not used
- Runtime claim: config/workspace lane only

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai render .
plugin-kit-ai render --check .
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform opencode --strict
```

## Target Files

- `targets/opencode/package.yaml`: authored OpenCode package metadata; `plugins` renders to `opencode.json.plugin`
- `targets/opencode/config.extra.json`: optional OpenCode config passthrough for non-managed fields
- `targets/opencode/commands/`: markdown commands mirrored into `.opencode/commands/`
- `targets/opencode/agents/`: markdown agents mirrored into `.opencode/agents/`
- `targets/opencode/themes/`: JSON theme definitions mirrored into `.opencode/themes/`
- portable `mcp/servers.json`: renders to `opencode.json.mcp`
- portable `skills/`: validated against the shared `SKILL.md` contract, then mirrored into `.opencode/skills/`
- `opencode.json`: rendered managed OpenCode workspace config

## Current Boundary

- Supported in v1: plugin package refs, shared MCP, portable skills, workspace commands, workspace agents, workspace themes, JSON/JSONC native config import, explicit `--include-user-scope` import, config passthrough
- Not first-class yet: `.opencode/plugins/**`, `.opencode/package.json`, local JS/TS plugin code, custom tools
- Native OpenCode config can be imported from `opencode.json` or `opencode.jsonc`; `.claude/skills` and `.agents/skills` are import-compatible sources only
- Unsupported local plugin code is warned-and-skipped rather than modeled as authored inputs
